<h2>A customizable log facility.<br /></h2>
<div>A simple hello world :<source type="cpp">  #include  &lt; yuni/core/logs.h &gt;

  int  main()
  {
         //  The  logger
         Yuni::Logs::Logger&lt;&gt;   logs;
         //  Hello  world  !
         logs. notice ()  &lt;&lt;  "Hello  world  !" ;
     return  0;
  }
</source>
<br /> This class uses a static decorator pattern to modify its behavior. By default, the output has the following format :<source type="cpp">  [date][color][verbosity  level][/color]  &lt;msg&gt;
</source>
 The color output from the shell is available for both Unix (Terminal) and Windows (cmd.exe).<br /><br />Parameters :<ul><li><code> TP</code> The Threading Policy<br /></li><li><code> Handlers</code> A static list of all message handlers<br /></li><li><code> Decorators</code> A static list of all decorators<br /></li></ul><br /></div>
